post_text:
Why the 2020 Census matters for schools. The 2020 Census count impacts the federal funds that communities receive each year for programs and services that are critical for schools, students, and younger children, such as:

- Special education, Head Start, after-school programs and classroom technology;
- Food assistance, including free and reduced-price school lunches;
- Maternal and child health programs.

